# GabaoIndex - GitHub Setup Guide

## 📋 Prerequisites

### 1. Install Git
Git is currently installing. Once complete, verify with:
```bash
git --version
```

**Alternative Installation Methods:**
- Download from: https://git-scm.com/download/win
- Or use Chocolatey: `choco install git`
- Or use Scoop: `scoop install git`

### 2. Create GitHub Account
If you don't have one: https://github.com/join

### 3. Install GitHub Desktop (Optional)
For GUI: https://desktop.github.com/

---

## 🚀 Step-by-Step GitHub Setup

### Step 1: Initialize Git Repository
```bash
cd C:\Users\beaud\Desktop\WebDev\Antigravity\gabonfind
git init
```

### Step 2: Configure Git
```bash
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your.email@example.com"
```

### Step 3: Create .gitignore File
Create a `.gitignore` file in your project root with:
```
# Dependencies
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# Runtime data
pids
*.pid
*.seed
*.pid.lock

# Coverage directory used by tools like istanbul
coverage/

# Logs
logs
*.log

# Environment variables
.env
.env.local
.env.development.local
.env.test.local
.env.production.local

# Editor directories and files
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# OS generated files
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db

# Temporary files
*.tmp
*.temp
```

### Step 4: Add Files to Git
```bash
git add .
```

### Step 5: Initial Commit
```bash
git commit -m "Initial commit: GabaoIndex Gabon directory website"
```

### Step 6: Create GitHub Repository

#### Option A: Using GitHub Website
1. Go to https://github.com/new
2. Repository name: `gabonfind` or `gaboaindex`
3. Description: `🌿 GabaoIndex - Complete Gabon business directory with 493+ listings`
4. Make it **Public** or **Private**
5. **DO NOT** initialize with README (we already have one)
6. Click **"Create repository"**

#### Option B: Using GitHub CLI (if installed)
```bash
gh repo create gabonfind --public --source=. --remote=origin --push
```

### Step 7: Connect Local Repository to GitHub
```bash
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/gabonfind.git
```

Replace `YOUR_USERNAME` with your actual GitHub username.

### Step 8: Push to GitHub
```bash
git push -u origin main
```

---

## 🔧 Troubleshooting

### "fatal: remote origin already exists"
If you get this error, remove the existing remote:
```bash
git remote remove origin
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/gabonfind.git
```

### "fatal: The current branch main has no upstream branch"
Push with upstream setup:
```bash
git push --set-upstream origin main
```

### Authentication Issues
GitHub now requires personal access tokens instead of passwords:

1. Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens
2. Generate new token with `repo` permissions
3. Use token as password when prompted

Or use SSH:
```bash
# Generate SSH key
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your.email@example.com"

# Add to GitHub: https://github.com/settings/keys
# Then use SSH URL:
git remote set-url origin git@github.com:YOUR_USERNAME/gabonfind.git
```

---

## 📁 Project Structure to Push

Your repository will contain:
```
gabonfind/
├── README.md                 # Deployment guide
├── NETLIFY_DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md
├── index.html               # Main website
├── admin.html              # Admin panel
├── style.css               # Styles
├── app.js                  # Main app logic
├── data.json              # 493+ listings
├── netlify.toml           # Netlify config
├── _redirects             # URL redirects
├── netlify/
│   └── functions/         # Serverless functions
│       ├── data.js
│       └── geocode.js
├── img/                   # Images
└── package.json           # Dependencies
```

---

## 🚀 Deploy to Netlify

Once pushed to GitHub:

1. Go to https://netlify.com
2. **"Add new site"** → **"Import an existing project"**
3. Connect your GitHub repository
4. Deploy settings will auto-detect
5. **Deploy!**

Your site will be live at: `https://gabonfind.netlify.app`

---

## 🔄 Future Updates

To push future changes:
```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Your commit message"
git push
```

